# Normalize all text files to LF in the repo AND the working tree.
# This repo is developed on a Windows cloud PC (core.autocrlf=true) but builds
# and deploys on Linux (Vercel). Without this, autocrlf rewrites working-tree
# files to CRLF on checkout, leaving git showing them "modified" with empty
# content diffs (phantom churn) — and any blanket `prettier --write` touches
# every file's mtime, amplifying it. eol=lf pins the working tree to LF so the
# churn cannot happen and Windows/Linux see identical bytes.
* text=auto eol=lf

# Shell scripts and hooks must be LF to execute.
*.sh text eol=lf
.husky/* text eol=lf

# Binary assets — never normalize or diff as text.
*.png binary
*.ico binary
*.ttf binary
*.otf binary
*.woff binary
*.woff2 binary
*.jpg binary
*.jpeg binary
*.webp binary
*.gif binary
*.pdf binary
